        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Vita",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", 38.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "θρησκείας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cultus religionis",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", potissimum ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "externus",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",” Grimm, so here and in the other places where it occurs in N.T., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Colossians 2:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jam 1:26-27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; twice in Wisdom, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Wis 14:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Wis 14:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", of the worship of idols; in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Sir 22:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the reading is doubtful; in 4Ma 5:6; 4Ma 5:13, of the religion of the Jews. The instances of its use both in Philo and Josephus show that it was plainly, distinguished from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εὐσεβεία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁσιότης",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Thus it is contrasted with the latter by Philo, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Quod det. potiori insid.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", c. 7: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "θρησκείαν ἀντὶ ὁσιότητος ἡγούμενος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and in Josephus it is frequently used of the public worship of God, worship in its external aspect, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ant.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ix., 13, 3; xii., 5, 4; v., 10, 1; xii., 6, 2. It was therefore a very natural word for St. Paul to use, and it is not necessary to suppose that he did so merely for the sake of Festus and the Romans (Blass), although the word was used of one mode of worship when contrasted with another; see further Hatch, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Essays in B.G.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", p. 55; Trench, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Synonyms",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", i., p. 200, and Mayor on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jam 1:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "φαρισαῖος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": emphatic at the end, expressing the “straitest sect” by name, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Galatians 1:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Php 3:5-6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
